<subSubSection id="E9AF48D2BF45FF841D95F8D59A92FE33" lastPageId="25" lastPageNumber="276" pageId="24" pageNumber="275" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="A10A1B59BF45FF841D95F8D59A56FEFB" blockId="24.[151,1437,1657,2007]" lastBlockId="25.[151,1437,151,501]" lastPageId="25" lastPageNumber="276" pageId="24" pageNumber="275">
<emphasis id="93C1C74BBF45FF851D95F8D59974F8F5" bold="true" box="[199,322,1873,1899]" pageId="24" pageNumber="275">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
Medium sized (TL: 
<quantity id="664DB6BCBF45FF851F6FF8D59AFBF8F2" box="[573,717,1873,1900]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="5.55" metricValueMax="5.7" metricValueMin="5.4" pageId="24" pageNumber="275" unit="mm" value="5.55" valueMax="5.7" valueMin="5.4">5.4–5.7 mm</quantity>
), oblong-oval species; dorsal surface distinctly convex. Head reddish, with dark band along eyes and infuscation on frons between eyes; pronotum reddish brown, laterally broadly testaceous; elytra brown, with very broad, irregularly shaped, transverse basal orange band. Pronotum with few short longitudinal strioles laterally. Each elytron with 11 superficially impressed discal striae: sutural stria usually strongly reduced to few short strioles, or almost absent in some specimens; all striae abbreviated posteriorly, striae 2, 3, 5, 7 and 9 ending in posterior fourth of elytral length, striae 4, 6, 8 and 11 reaching apical fourth of elytral length; striae 7 and 9 often fragmented to strioles throughout their length (
<figureCitation id="398E07DCBF44FF841E98FF5B9C2BFF67" box="[970,1053,223,249]" captionStart="FIGURES 25–28" captionStartId="37.[151,264,1943,1967]" captionTargetBox="[230,1356,193,1907]" captionTargetId="figure-18@37.[217,1370,181,1919]" captionTargetPageId="37" captionText="FIGURES 25–28. Habitus of Copelatus in China. 25. C. weymarni (♂; Kaymanovka, Russia); 26. C. xiniudong sp. nov. (holotype ♂; Xiniudong, Guizhou); 27. C. zimmermanni (♀; Danxia Shan, Guangdong); 28. C. sp. (♀; Lantau, Hongkong). Scale bar 1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6411114" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6411114/files/figure.png" pageId="25" pageNumber="276">Fig. 27</figureCitation>
). Median lobe broad, club-shaped, with two protuberances on dorsal side, sinuate on ventral margin; apex beak-shaped (
<figureCitation id="398E07DCBF44FF84193EFE879CF5FE80" box="[1132,1219,259,286]" captionStart="FIGURES 63–70" captionStartId="41.[151,264,1403,1427]" captionTargetBox="[216,1366,200,1362]" captionTargetId="figure-18@41.[205,1383,181,1379]" captionTargetPageId="41" captionText="FIGURES 63–70. Male genitalia of Copelatus. 63, 65, 67, 69. median lobe in lateral view; 64, 66, 68, 70. paramere. 63–64. C. tengchongensis sp. nov. (holotype, Beihai, Yunnan); 65–66. C. weymarni (Honshu, Japan); 67–68. C. xiniudong sp. nov. (holotype, Xiniudong, Guizhou); 69–70. C. zimmermanni (Danxiashan, Guangdong). Scale bar 0.5 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6410764" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6410764/files/figure.png" pageId="25" pageNumber="276">Fig. 69</figureCitation>
). Paramere slender ‘C’-shaped; apex slender; apical lobe long, club-shaped (
<figureCitation id="398E07DCBF44FF841E5FFEA39B6CFEDF" box="[781,858,295,321]" captionStart="FIGURES 63–70" captionStartId="41.[151,264,1403,1427]" captionTargetBox="[216,1366,200,1362]" captionTargetId="figure-18@41.[205,1383,181,1379]" captionTargetPageId="41" captionText="FIGURES 63–70. Male genitalia of Copelatus. 63, 65, 67, 69. median lobe in lateral view; 64, 66, 68, 70. paramere. 63–64. C. tengchongensis sp. nov. (holotype, Beihai, Yunnan); 65–66. C. weymarni (Honshu, Japan); 67–68. C. xiniudong sp. nov. (holotype, Xiniudong, Guizhou); 69–70. C. zimmermanni (Danxiashan, Guangdong). Scale bar 0.5 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6410764" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6410764/files/figure.png" pageId="25" pageNumber="276">Fig 70</figureCitation>
). Female similar to male; strioles on pronotum more numerous, elytral striae more impressed.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="A10A1B59BF44FF841D95FEEA9A92FE33" blockId="25.[151,1437,151,501]" pageId="25" pageNumber="276">
<emphasis id="93C1C74BBF44FF841D95FEEA99A8FE16" bold="true" box="[199,414,366,392]" pageId="25" pageNumber="276">Collection details.</emphasis>
The specimens from Danxiashan were collected in shallow open pool with sparse littoral vegetation, and in a pool on a stream (
<figureCitation id="398E07DCBF44FF841F11FE179AA1FE33" box="[579,663,403,429]" captionStart="FIGURES 71–78" captionStartId="42.[151,264,1872,1896]" captionTargetBox="[180,1408,181,1848]" captionTargetId="figure-23@42.[180,1408,181,1848]" captionTargetPageId="42" captionText="FIGURES 71–78. Habitat of Copelatus in China. 71. Tianmushan, Zhejiang (C. chinensis); 72. Jinggangshan, Jiangxi (C. dentatipenis sp. nov.); 73. Tongbiguan, Yunnan (C. diversistriatus sp. nov.). 74. Dadongshan, Guangdong (C. nanlingensis sp. nov.); 75. Macao (C. oblitus in wet soil); 76. Dali, Yunnan (C. rimosus); 77. Kongshu, Yunnan (C. rosulae sp. nov.); 78. Danxiashan, Guangdong (C. oblitus and C. zimmermanni)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6411118" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6411118/files/figure.png" pageId="25" pageNumber="276">Fig. 78</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="E9AF48D2BF44FF841D95FE329C40FE6B" pageId="25" pageNumber="276" type="distribution">
<paragraph id="A10A1B59BF44FF841D95FE329C40FE6B" blockId="25.[151,1437,151,501]" pageId="25" pageNumber="276">
<emphasis id="93C1C74BBF44FF841D95FE329957FE4E" bold="true" box="[199,353,438,464]" pageId="25" pageNumber="276">Distribution.</emphasis>
A species described from 
<collectingRegion id="6371D5BBBF44FF841FC9FE339AC9FE4F" box="[667,767,439,465]" country="China" name="Zhejiang" pageId="25" pageNumber="276">Zhejiang</collectingRegion>
(
<collectingCountry id="D9A25BC9BF44FF841E40FE339B6CFE4C" box="[786,858,439,466]" name="China" pageId="25" pageNumber="276">China</collectingCountry>
), and subsequently recorded also from 
<collectingCountry id="D9A25BC9BF44FF84187BFE339D5FFE4F" box="[1321,1385,439,465]" name="Japan" pageId="25" pageNumber="276">Japan</collectingCountry>
and 
<collectingCountry id="D9A25BC9BF44FF841DC5FE5F98EDFE6B" box="[151,219,475,501]" name="South Korea" pageId="25" pageNumber="276">Korea</collectingCountry>
(
<bibRefCitation id="C52466A8BF44FF841DB8FE5F9956FE6B" author="Sato, M." box="[234,352,474,501]" pageId="25" pageNumber="276" pagination="57 - 67" refId="ref33445" refString="Sato, M. (1985) The genus Copelatus of Japan (Coleoptera: Dytiscidae). Transactions of the Shikoku Entomological Society, 17, 57 - 67." type="journal article" year="1985">Satô 1985</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation id="C52466A8BF44FF841C39FE5F9A17FE6B" author="Park, H. C. &amp; Lee, Y. B. &amp; Lee, H. A." box="[363,545,475,501]" pageId="25" pageNumber="276" pagination="73 - 76" refId="ref33262" refString="Park, H. C., Lee, Y. B. &amp; Lee, H. A. (2008) Taxonomic review of the genus Copelatus Erichson (Coleoptera: Dytiscidae) in Korea. Entomological Research, 38 (1), 73 - 76. https: // doi. org / 10.1111 / j. 1748 - 5967.2008.00134. x" type="journal article" year="2008">
Park 
<emphasis id="93C1C74BBF44FF841CF7FE5F99EBFE6B" box="[421,477,475,501]" italics="true" pageId="25" pageNumber="276">et al.</emphasis>
2008
</bibRefCitation>
). 
<emphasis id="93C1C74BBF44FF841F61FE5E9C30FE6A" bold="true" box="[563,1030,474,501]" pageId="25" pageNumber="276">First record from Guangdong province</emphasis>
(
<figureCitation id="398E07DCBF44FF841947FE5F9C5FFE6B" box="[1045,1129,475,501]" captionStart="FIGURE 83" captionStartId="44.[151,250,2008,2032]" captionTargetBox="[273,1315,1132,1980]" captionTargetId="figure-39@44.[267,1320,1127,1984]" captionTargetPageId="44" captionText="FIGURE 83. Map of distribution of Copelatus in China Mainland." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6410823" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6410823/files/figure.png" pageId="25" pageNumber="276">Fig. 83</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
